<dl id="n34070a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n34" href="#n34070a">N34 (VI.B.27)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n34all.htm#n34070a"> 70(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ each side being / infinitely small <small>Blue</small> </blockquote> <dd class="well"><mm class="note">Note: Geometry: A method to calculate the circumference of a circle: determine the limit to which the length of the perimeter of an inscribed (or circumscribed) regular polygon tends when the number of its sides is made infinitely large (in which case the length of each side becomes infinitely small). Used at <a name="n34072a" href="n34all.htm#n34072a">N34 (VI.B.27):072(a)</a> and <a name="n34073a" href="n34all.htm#n34073a">N34 (VI.B.27):073(a)</a>. </mm> </dd></dl>
